==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[προπαροξυτονος]], from [[προ-]] + [[παροξυτονος]] ‘paroxytone, penultimate’, from [[παρα-]] + [[οξυτονος]] ‘word with stress on final syllable’, from [[οξυς]] ‘sharp, acute’ + [[τονος]] ‘pitch, accent’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /prəʊpə'rɒksɪtəʊn/

===Adjective===
'''proparoxytone'''
# pertaining to a word in ancient Greek with an acute [[accent]] on the [[antepenultimate]] syllable
# pertaining to a word in any language with [[antepenultimate]] stress

===Noun===
{{en-noun|proparoxytone|proparoxytones}}
# a proparoxytone word